001.Black_footed_Albatross.description: A large seabird with dark brown to black plumage, white around the base of the bill and under the eye. Has a large wingspan and is an excellent glider.

002.Laysan_Albatross.description: Large seabird with white head and body, dark back and wings. Has distinctive dark eye patch.

003.Sooty_Albatross.description: Large seabird with dark sooty-brown to blackish plumage. Has white crescent behind eye.

004.Groove_billed_Ani.description: Large black bird with long tail, grooved bill, and iridescent black plumage.

005.Crested_Auklet.description: Small seabird with black body, white belly, and distinctive forward-curving crest on forehead.

006.Least_Auklet.description: Very small seabird, smallest auklet. Black above, white below, with white facial plumes in breeding season.

007.Parakeet_Auklet.description: Small seabird with dark gray body, white belly, and distinctive upturned red bill.

008.Rhinoceros_Auklet.description: Medium-sized seabird with dark gray-brown body, white belly, and distinctive horn-like projection on bill during breeding.

009.Brewer_Blackbird.description: Medium-sized blackbird. Males are black with purple-blue iridescence. Females are brown with dark eyes.

010.Red_winged_Blackbird.description: Medium-sized blackbird. Males are black with red and yellow shoulder patches. Females are streaked brown and black.

011.Rusty_Blackbird.description: Medium-sized blackbird. Breeding males are black with greenish iridescence. Females are brown with rusty edges.

012.Yellow_headed_Blackbird.description: Medium-sized blackbird. Males are black with bright yellow head and chest. Females are brown with yellow throat.

013.Bobolink.description: Medium-sized songbird. Breeding males are black with white back and yellow nape. Females and winter males are streaked brown.

014.Indigo_Bunting.description: Small songbird. Breeding males are brilliant blue all over. Females and winter males are brown with blue tinges.

015.Lazuli_Bunting.description: Small songbird. Males have bright blue head and back, orange breast, white belly. Females are brown with blue tinges.

016.Painted_Bunting.description: Small, colorful songbird. Males are brightly colored with blue head, green back, red underparts. Females are green above, yellow-green below.

017.Cardinal.description: Medium-sized songbird. Males are bright red with black face mask and crested head. Females are brown with red tinges.

018.Spotted_Catbird.description: Medium-sized bird with olive-green plumage and white spots. Has distinctive cat-like call.

019.Gray_Catbird.description: Medium-sized songbird. Slate gray overall with black cap and chestnut undertail coverts.

020.Yellow_breasted_Chat.description: Large warbler with bright yellow breast, olive-green back, white spectacles, and long tail.

021.Eastern_Towhee.description: Large sparrow. Males are black above with white spots, rufous sides, and white belly. Females are brown where males are black.

022.Chuck_will_Widow.description: Large nightjar with mottled brown and gray plumage, large eyes, and wide mouth.

023.Brandt_Cormorant.description: Large seabird with black body, blue throat patch in breeding season, and long tail.

024.Red_faced_Cormorant.description: Large seabird with black body, red face in breeding season, and white flank patches.

025.Pelagic_Cormorant.description: Medium-sized seabird with black body, white flank patches, and red face in breeding season.

026.Bronzed_Cowbird.description: Medium-sized blackbird. Males are black with bronzy iridescence and red eyes. Females are brown.

027.Shiny_Cowbird.description: Small blackbird. Males are black with purple-blue iridescence. Females are brown.

028.Brown_Creeper.description: Small bird with brown mottled upperparts, white underparts, and curved bill. Climbs up tree trunks.

029.American_Crow.description: Large, all-black bird with thick bill and fan-shaped tail.

030.Fish_Crow.description: Medium-sized, all-black bird similar to American Crow but smaller with higher-pitched call.

031.Black_billed_Cuckoo.description: Medium-sized bird with brown upperparts, white underparts, and long tail with white spots.

032.Mangrove_Cuckoo.description: Medium-sized bird with brown upperparts, buff underparts, and long tail with white spots.

033.Yellow_billed_Cuckoo.description: Medium-sized bird with brown upperparts, white underparts, and long tail with large white spots.

034.Gray_crowned_Rosy_Finch.description: Medium-sized finch with gray crown, brown body, and pink patches on wings and rump. Bill is yellow in summer, dark in winter.

035.Purple_Finch.description: Medium-sized finch. Males are raspberry-red on head, breast, and back. Females are streaked brown with white eyebrow.

036.Northern_Flicker.description: Large woodpecker. Brown with black bars, white rump, and yellow or red under wings. Has black crescent on chest.

037.Acadian_Flycatcher.description: Small flycatcher with olive-green upperparts, white underparts, and two white wing bars.

038.Great_Crested_Flycatcher.description: Large flycatcher with gray head, olive-brown back, yellow belly, and rufous tail.

039.Least_Flycatcher.description: Small flycatcher with olive-gray upperparts, white underparts, and two white wing bars.

040.Olive_sided_Flycatcher.description: Large flycatcher with dark olive-gray upperparts, white underparts with dark sides, and white tufts on back.

041.Scissor_tailed_Flycatcher.description: Medium-sized flycatcher with gray head, white underparts, salmon-pink sides, and very long forked tail.

042.Vermilion_Flycatcher.description: Small flycatcher. Males are bright red with dark brown back and wings. Females are brown with red underparts.

043.Yellow_bellied_Flycatcher.description: Small flycatcher with olive-green upperparts, yellow underparts, and two white wing bars.

044.Frigatebird.description: Very large seabird with black body, long pointed wings, deeply forked tail, and red throat pouch (males).

045.Northern_Fulmar.description: Medium-sized seabird with gray and white plumage, thick bill, and tube-like nostrils.

046.Gadwall.description: Medium-sized dabbling duck. Males are gray with black rear, white speculum. Females are mottled brown.

047.American_Goldfinch.description: Small finch. Breeding males are bright yellow with black cap, wings, and tail. Females and winter males are duller, olive-brown with yellow highlights.

048.European_Goldfinch.description: Small finch with red face, black and white head, brown back, and yellow wing patches.

049.Boat_tailed_Grackle.description: Large blackbird with long tail, iridescent black plumage, and yellow eyes.

050.Eared_Grebe.description: Small grebe with black head and neck, golden ear tufts in breeding season, and red eyes.

051.Horned_Grebe.description: Small grebe with black head, golden ear tufts, red eyes, and chestnut neck in breeding season.

052.Pied_billed_Grebe.description: Small grebe with brown body, black ring around bill in breeding season, and short tail.

053.Western_Grebe.description: Large grebe with long neck, black cap, white face and neck, and red eyes.

054.Blue_Grosbeak.description: Medium-sized songbird. Males are deep blue with chestnut wing bars. Females are brown with blue tinges.

055.Evening_Grosbeak.description: Large finch. Males are yellow with black head, wings, and tail. Females are gray with yellow highlights.

056.Pine_Grosbeak.description: Large finch. Males are rose-red with gray wings and tail. Females are gray with yellow-orange highlights.

057.Rose_breasted_Grosbeak.description: Medium-sized songbird. Males are black and white with rose-red breast. Females are streaked brown.

058.Pigeon_Guillemot.description: Medium-sized seabird with black body, white wing patches, and red feet.

059.California_Gull.description: Medium-sized gull with white head and body, gray back, yellow bill with black and red spots, and yellow legs.

060.Glaucous_winged_Gull.description: Large gull with white head and body, gray back, and pale gray wings (no black tips).

061.Heermann_Gull.description: Medium-sized gull with dark gray body, white head, and red bill with black tip.

062.Herring_Gull.description: Large gull with white head and body, gray back, yellow bill with red spot, and pink legs.

063.Ivory_Gull.description: Medium-sized gull with entirely white plumage, black legs, and yellow-tipped bill.

064.Ring_billed_Gull.description: Medium-sized gull with white head and body, gray back, yellow bill with black ring, and yellow legs.

065.Slaty_backed_Gull.description: Very large gull with white head and body, dark slate-gray back, and pink legs.

066.Western_Gull.description: Large gull with white head and body, dark gray back, yellow bill with red spot, and pink legs.

067.Anna_Hummingbird.description: Medium-sized hummingbird. Males have iridescent rose-red crown and throat. Females are green above, gray below with red spots on throat.

068.Ruby_throated_Hummingbird.description: Small hummingbird. Males have iridescent red throat, green back, and white underparts. Females lack red throat.

069.Rufous_Hummingbird.description: Small hummingbird. Males are rufous (reddish-brown) overall with iridescent red throat. Females are green above, rufous below.

070.Green_Violetear.description: Medium-sized hummingbird with green body, violet ear patches, and blue tail.

071.Long_tailed_Jaeger.description: Medium-sized seabird with gray-brown body, long pointed tail, and white underparts.

072.Pomarine_Jaeger.description: Large seabird with dark brown body, white wing flashes, and twisted tail streamers.

073.Blue_Jay.description: Large songbird with blue upperparts, white face and underparts, black collar, and crested head.

074.Florida_Jay.description: Medium-sized jay with blue head, wings, and tail, gray back, and white underparts.

075.Green_Jay.description: Medium-sized jay with green upperparts, yellow underparts, blue head, and black throat.

076.Dark_eyed_Junco.description: Medium-sized sparrow. Slate-gray or brown above, white below, with pink bill. Several color variations.

077.Tropical_Kingbird.description: Large flycatcher with gray head, olive back, yellow underparts, and notched tail.

078.Gray_Kingbird.description: Large flycatcher with gray head and back, white underparts, and notched tail.

079.Belted_Kingfisher.description: Large kingfisher with blue-gray upperparts, white underparts, and shaggy crest. Females have rufous belly band.

080.Green_Kingfisher.description: Small kingfisher with green upperparts, white underparts with green spots, and long bill.

081.Pied_Kingfisher.description: Medium-sized kingfisher with black and white plumage, crested head, and long bill.

082.Ringed_Kingfisher.description: Very large kingfisher with blue-gray upperparts, white collar, rufous underparts, and shaggy crest.

083.White_breasted_Kingfisher.description: Large kingfisher with bright blue back, white breast, rufous head, and long red bill.

084.Red_legged_Kittiwake.description: Small gull with white head and body, gray back, black wing tips, and red legs.

085.Horned_Lark.description: Small lark with brown upperparts, pale underparts, black face mask, and small black 'horns' on head.

086.Pacific_Loon.description: Large loon with black head and neck, white underparts, and gray back with white spots.

087.Mallard.description: Large dabbling duck. Males have green head, yellow bill, brown breast, and gray body. Females are mottled brown.

088.Western_Meadowlark.description: Medium-sized songbird with yellow underparts, black V on breast, and brown streaked back.

089.Hooded_Merganser.description: Small diving duck. Males have black and white crested head, brown sides, and white breast. Females have brown crested head.

090.Red_breasted_Merganser.description: Medium-sized diving duck. Males have dark green head, white collar, and rusty breast. Females have brown crested head.

091.Mockingbird.description: Medium-sized songbird. Gray above, white below, with white wing patches and long tail.

092.Nighthawk.description: Medium-sized nightjar with mottled gray and brown plumage, white wing patches, and large eyes.

093.Clark_Nutcracker.description: Large songbird with gray body, black wings with white patches, and long pointed bill.

094.White_breasted_Nuthatch.description: Medium-sized nuthatch with blue-gray upperparts, white face and underparts, and black cap.

095.Baltimore_Oriole.description: Medium-sized songbird. Males are bright orange with black head, back, and wings. Females are orange-yellow with dark wings.

096.Hooded_Oriole.description: Medium-sized oriole. Males are orange-yellow with black face, throat, and back. Females are yellow-olive.

097.Orchard_Oriole.description: Small oriole. Males are dark chestnut with black head and throat. Females are olive-yellow with dark wings.

098.Scott_Oriole.description: Medium-sized oriole. Males are black with yellow head, breast, and rump. Females are olive-yellow.

099.Ovenbird.description: Large warbler with olive-brown upperparts, white underparts with dark streaks, and orange crown stripe.

100.Brown_Pelican.description: Large seabird with brown body, white head and neck, and huge bill with expandable pouch.

101.White_Pelican.description: Very large white bird with black wing tips, huge bill, and expandable pouch.

102.Western_Wood_Pewee.description: Medium-sized flycatcher with olive-gray upperparts, white underparts, and two white wing bars.

103.Sayornis.description: Medium-sized flycatcher with brown-gray upperparts, white underparts, and dark head.

104.American_Pipit.description: Small bird with streaked brown upperparts, white underparts with streaks, and white outer tail feathers.

105.Whip_poor_Will.description: Medium-sized nightjar with mottled brown and gray plumage, large eyes, and wide mouth.

106.Horned_Puffin.description: Medium-sized seabird with black body, white face, large colorful bill, and yellow horn-like projections above eyes.

107.Common_Raven.description: Very large, all-black bird with thick bill, shaggy throat feathers, and wedge-shaped tail.

108.White_necked_Raven.description: Large, all-black bird with white patch on back of neck, thick bill, and wedge-shaped tail.

109.American_Redstart.description: Small warbler. Males are black with orange patches on wings, tail, and sides. Females are gray with yellow patches.

110.Geococcyx.description: Large ground-dwelling bird with brown and white streaked plumage, long tail, and strong legs.

111.Loggerhead_Shrike.description: Medium-sized songbird with gray head and back, white underparts, black mask, and hooked bill.

112.Great_Grey_Shrike.description: Large shrike with gray head and back, white underparts, black mask, and hooked bill.

113.Baird_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with streaked brown back, buffy underparts with fine streaks, and central crown stripe.

114.Black_throated_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with black throat, white eyebrow, and gray body.

115.Brewer_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with gray head, brown back with streaks, and white underparts.

116.Chipping_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with rufous cap, gray face, and brown streaked back.

117.Clay_colored_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with gray head with brown crown stripe, pale brown back, and buff underparts.

118.House_Sparrow.description: Small, chunky bird. Males have gray crown, black bib, and chestnut nape. Females are streaked brown and gray.

119.Field_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with pink bill, gray head with rufous crown, and brown streaked back.

120.Fox_Sparrow.description: Large sparrow with heavily streaked brown and gray plumage, rufous tail, and spotted breast.

121.Grasshopper_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with flat head, short tail, and buffy underparts with fine streaks.

122.Harris_Sparrow.description: Large sparrow with black face and bib, pink bill, and brown streaked back.

123.Henslow_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with olive head, brown streaked back, and buffy underparts with streaks.

124.Le_Conte_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with orange face, gray crown with central stripe, and buffy underparts with fine streaks.

125.Lincoln_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with gray face with brown crown, buffy breast with fine streaks, and brown streaked back.

126.Nelson_Sharp_tailed_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with orange face, gray crown, and buffy underparts with fine streaks.

127.Savannah_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with yellow eyebrow, streaked brown back, and white underparts with streaks.

128.Seaside_Sparrow.description: Medium-sized sparrow with gray head, olive back, and white underparts with dark streaks.

129.Song_Sparrow.description: Medium-sized sparrow with streaked brown back, white underparts with dark central spot, and brown streaks.

130.Tree_Sparrow.description: Small sparrow with rufous crown, gray face with dark spot, and brown streaked back.

131.Vesper_Sparrow.description: Medium-sized sparrow with streaked brown back, white outer tail feathers, and white eye ring.

132.White_crowned_Sparrow.description: Large sparrow with black and white striped crown, gray face, and brown streaked back.

133.White_throated_Sparrow.description: Large sparrow with black and white striped crown, white throat, and yellow spot between eye and bill.

134.Cape_Glossy_Starling.description: Medium-sized starling with iridescent blue-green plumage, yellow eyes, and long tail.

135.Bank_Swallow.description: Small swallow with brown upperparts, white underparts, and brown breast band.

136.Barn_Swallow.description: Medium-sized swallow with blue upperparts, rufous underparts, and deeply forked tail.

137.Cliff_Swallow.description: Medium-sized swallow with blue upperparts, buff rump, white underparts, and square tail.

138.Tree_Swallow.description: Medium-sized swallow with blue-green upperparts, white underparts, and slightly forked tail.

139.Scarlet_Tanager.description: Medium-sized songbird. Breeding males are bright red with black wings and tail. Females are olive-yellow.

140.Summer_Tanager.description: Medium-sized songbird. Males are entirely red. Females are olive-yellow with orange tinges.

141.Artic_Tern.description: Medium-sized tern with white body, gray wings, black cap, and red bill and legs.

142.Black_Tern.description: Small tern. Breeding adults are black with gray wings. Non-breeding adults are white with black cap.

143.Caspian_Tern.description: Very large tern with white body, gray wings, black cap, and large red bill.

144.Common_Tern.description: Medium-sized tern with white body, gray wings, black cap, and red bill with black tip.

145.Elegant_Tern.description: Medium-sized tern with white body, gray wings, black cap, and long orange bill.

146.Forsters_Tern.description: Medium-sized tern with white body, gray wings, black cap, and orange bill with black tip.

147.Least_Tern.description: Very small tern with white body, gray wings, black cap, and yellow bill with black tip.

148.Green_tailed_Towhee.description: Large sparrow with green tail, rufous cap, white throat, and gray body.

149.Brown_Thrasher.description: Large songbird with reddish-brown upperparts, streaked white underparts, long tail, and curved bill.

150.Sage_Thrasher.description: Medium-sized songbird with gray-brown upperparts, white underparts with dark streaks, and long tail.

151.Black_capped_Vireo.description: Small vireo with black cap, white eye ring, and olive-yellow body.

152.Blue_headed_Vireo.description: Small vireo with blue-gray head, white spectacles, olive back, and yellow sides.

153.Philadelphia_Vireo.description: Small vireo with olive upperparts, yellow underparts, gray head, and white eyebrow stripe.

154.Red_eyed_Vireo.description: Medium-sized vireo with olive-green upperparts, white underparts, gray crown, and red eyes.

155.Warbling_Vireo.description: Small vireo with gray head, olive back, white underparts, and faint eye stripe.

156.White_eyed_Vireo.description: Small vireo with gray head, yellow spectacles, white eyes, and olive-yellow body.

157.Yellow_throated_Vireo.description: Medium-sized vireo with yellow throat and breast, gray head, and olive back.

158.Bay_breasted_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Breeding males have chestnut crown and sides, black face, and yellow nape.

159.Black_and_white_Warbler.description: Small warbler with black and white striped plumage, resembling a zebra. Creeps along tree trunks.

160.Black_throated_Blue_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Males are blue above with black face and throat, white underparts. Females are olive with white wing spot.

161.Blue_winged_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Males have yellow head and underparts, blue-gray wings with white bars, and olive back.

162.Canada_Warbler.description: Small warbler with yellow underparts, gray upperparts, and black necklace on yellow breast.

163.Cape_May_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Breeding males have yellow head with chestnut cheek patch, streaked yellow underparts, and white wing patches.

164.Cerulean_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Males are blue above with white underparts and black streaks. Females are blue-gray.

165.Chestnut_sided_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Breeding males have yellow crown, black face, white underparts, and chestnut sides. Females are duller.

166.Golden_winged_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Males have yellow crown, black face, white wing patches, and gray body.

167.Hooded_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Males have black hood, yellow face, and yellow underparts. Females lack hood.

168.Kentucky_Warbler.description: Medium-sized warbler with olive upperparts, yellow underparts, black mask, and yellow spectacles.

169.Magnolia_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Breeding males have black back with white wing bars, yellow underparts with black streaks, and white tail patches.

170.Mourning_Warbler.description: Medium-sized warbler with olive upperparts, yellow underparts, and gray hood with black bib.

171.Myrtle_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Breeding males have yellow rump, yellow crown patch, white throat, and streaked sides.

172.Nashville_Warbler.description: Small warbler with olive upperparts, yellow underparts, gray head, and white eye ring.

173.Orange_crowned_Warbler.description: Small warbler with olive-yellow upperparts, yellow underparts, and faint orange crown patch.

174.Palm_Warbler.description: Small warbler with brown cap, yellow underparts with streaks, and constantly bobs tail.

175.Pine_Warbler.description: Small warbler with olive-yellow upperparts, yellow underparts with faint streaks, and white wing bars.

176.Prairie_Warbler.description: Small warbler with olive upperparts, yellow underparts with black streaks, and chestnut streaks on back.

177.Prothonotary_Warbler.description: Medium-sized warbler with bright yellow head and underparts, blue-gray wings, and olive back.

178.Swainson_Warbler.description: Medium-sized warbler with brown upperparts, white underparts, and brown crown stripe.

179.Tennessee_Warbler.description: Small warbler with olive upperparts, white underparts, gray head, and white eyebrow stripe.

180.Wilson_Warbler.description: Small warbler with olive upperparts, yellow underparts, and black cap (males) or olive cap (females).

181.Worm_eating_Warbler.description: Medium-sized warbler with olive upperparts, buff underparts, and black and buff striped head.

182.Yellow_Warbler.description: Small warbler. Males are bright yellow with reddish streaks on breast. Females are duller yellow.

183.Northern_Waterthrush.description: Large warbler with brown upperparts, white underparts with dark streaks, and white eyebrow stripe.

184.Louisiana_Waterthrush.description: Large warbler with brown upperparts, white underparts with dark streaks, and white eyebrow stripe.

185.Bohemian_Waxwing.description: Medium-sized songbird similar to Cedar Waxwing but larger, with gray belly and white wing patches.

186.Cedar_Waxwing.description: Medium-sized songbird with sleek brown body, yellow-tipped tail, red waxy wing tips, and black mask.

187.American_Three_toed_Woodpecker.description: Medium-sized woodpecker with black and white barred back, yellow crown patch (males), and three toes.

188.Pileated_Woodpecker.description: Very large woodpecker with black body, white stripes on face, and red crest. Males have red mustache.

189.Red_bellied_Woodpecker.description: Medium-sized woodpecker with black and white barred back, red cap and nape, and pale belly.

190.Red_cockaded_Woodpecker.description: Medium-sized woodpecker with black and white barred back, white cheek patches, and small red spot on head (males).

191.Red_headed_Woodpecker.description: Medium-sized woodpecker with entirely red head, black and white body, and white wing patches.

192.Downy_Woodpecker.description: Small woodpecker with black and white plumage, white back, and small bill. Males have red nape patch.

193.Bewick_Wren.description: Small wren with brown upperparts, white underparts, and long tail with white corners.

194.Cactus_Wren.description: Large wren with brown upperparts with white spots, white underparts with dark spots, and long tail.

195.Carolina_Wren.description: Large wren with reddish-brown upperparts, buff underparts, and white eyebrow stripe.

196.House_Wren.description: Small, brown wren with barred wings and tail. Short, slightly curved bill.

197.Marsh_Wren.description: Small wren with brown upperparts with white streaks, white underparts, and short tail.

198.Rock_Wren.description: Medium-sized wren with gray-brown upperparts, buff underparts, and long tail.

199.Winter_Wren.description: Very small wren with brown mottled upperparts, buff underparts, and short tail.

200.Common_Yellowthroat.description: Small warbler. Males have black mask, yellow throat, and olive back. Females lack mask.

ADONIS.description: Small butterfly with bright blue upperwings (males) or brown upperwings (females), and orange spots on hindwings.

AFRICAN GIANT SWALLOWTAIL.description: Very large butterfly with black and yellow wings, long tail-like extensions on hindwings, and distinctive wing pattern.

AMERICAN SNOOT.description: Small butterfly with long snout-like projection on head, brown wings with orange patches, and white spots.

AN 88.description: Small butterfly with black and white wings, distinctive '88' or '89' pattern on hindwings, and red markings.

APPOLLO.description: Large butterfly with white wings, black spots, red eye-spots on hindwings, and transparent wing tips.

ARCIGERA FLOWER MOTH.description: Medium-sized moth with brown and white patterned wings, and distinctive flower-like markings.

ATALA.description: Small butterfly with black wings, blue-green iridescent spots, and red abdomen.

ATLAS MOTH.description: Very large moth with brown, red, and white patterned wings, and distinctive snake-like wing tips.

BANDED ORANGE HELICONIAN.description: Medium-sized butterfly with orange and black banded wings, and long narrow shape.

BANDED PEACOCK.description: Medium-sized butterfly with brown wings, white bands, and distinctive eye-spots on hindwings.

BANDED TIGER MOTH.description: Medium-sized moth with black and white banded wings, and orange or yellow markings.

BECKERS WHITE.description: Small butterfly with white wings, black spots on forewings, and gray-green undersides.

BIRD CHERRY ERMINE MOTH.description: Small white moth with black spots, and distinctive ermine-like pattern.

BLACK HAIRSTREAK.description: Small butterfly with brown wings, orange band on hindwings, and white-tipped tail.

BLUE MORPHO.description: Very large butterfly with brilliant blue iridescent upperwings and brown undersides with eye-spots.

BLUE SPOTTED CROW.description: Medium-sized butterfly with dark brown or black wings, blue spots, and white markings.

BROOKES BIRDWING.description: Very large butterfly with black and green wings (males) or brown wings (females), and long tail-like extensions.

BROWN ARGUS.description: Small butterfly with brown wings, orange spots on hindwings, and white fringes.

BROWN SIPROETA.description: Medium-sized butterfly with brown wings, orange bands, and distinctive eye-spots.

CABBAGE WHITE.description: Small butterfly with white wings, black spots on forewings (males) or two spots (females), and yellow-green undersides.

CAIRNS BIRDWING.description: Very large butterfly with black and green wings (males) or brown wings (females), and long tail-like extensions.

CHALK HILL BLUE.description: Small butterfly with blue upperwings (males) or brown upperwings (females), and distinctive white fringes.

CHECQUERED SKIPPER.description: Small butterfly with brown and orange checkered wings, and distinctive pattern.

CHESTNUT.description: Small butterfly with brown wings, orange patches, and eye-spots on hindwings.

CINNABAR MOTH.description: Medium-sized moth with black and red wings, and distinctive warning colors.

CLEARWING MOTH.description: Medium-sized moth with transparent wings, yellow and black body, and wasp-like appearance.

CLEOPATRA.description: Medium-sized butterfly with yellow wings (males) or greenish-white wings (females), and distinctive shape.

CLODIUS PARNASSIAN.description: Large butterfly with white wings, black spots, red eye-spots on hindwings, and transparent wing tips.

CLOUDED SULPHUR.description: Medium-sized butterfly with yellow wings (males) or white/yellow wings (females), and black borders.

COMET MOTH.description: Very large moth with yellow and brown wings, long tail-like extensions, and distinctive eye-spots.
